snippet.textDisplay: A reason that Todd could have left her ex-husband, Dicicco, only a $1 in her will could be so he wouldn't be able to dispute the will in court to get money, under the pretense that she "forgot" to include him. This way, by only giving him a dollar, it shows proof that she did not in fact forget about him, so he wouldn't be able to take it to court to get any of her money after her death. This is something I've seen in modern day used so family members you don't like won't be able to get any of your money under the excuse that you "forgot" to include them.
